The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Bablu Dalui, 35, hacked wife Swapna, 28, early on Monday and then committed suicide in Palora village, under Uluberia police station, in Howrah. Police said Bablu?s body was found floating in a pond near his residence. It was sent for post-mortem. 

 eighbours said Bablu, an alcoholic, used to beat his wife regularly on suspicion that she was having an affair. Around 2 am, he slashed Swapna after an altercation. Later, neighbours said, he consumed poison and drowned himself in the pond.

 wapna was taken to the Uluberia sub-divisional hospital, where her condition was stated to be critical. An inquiry has been ordered.

 Fire services minister Pratim Chatterjee on Monday said fire-safety norms were not adhered to while setting up the Bantala-based Calcutta Leather Complex. Chatterjee, who inspected the complex in the morning, said the zone had no provision for hydrants. His department was not consulted while the plan was being drawn up. Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will inaugurate the complex on June 20.

 Mangal Goswami, 39, an assistant sub-inspector at Bally police station, was killed by a truck on GT Road around 6.30 am on Monday. The police officer was heading for a tea stall, opposite the police station, when the truck crushed him. The driver fled. 

 The Calcutta Municipal Corporation has opened the assessment department?s cash counters at the Gariahat office to enable property owners in the area to deposit supplementary tax bills. The facilities were available only at the civic headquarters on SN Banerjee Road. Civic commissioner Debashis Som said the daily collection of supplementary property tax had touched Rs 3 lakh. The authorities have installed a vault for the assessment department at the Gariahat office.

 A woman died after being knocked down by a private bus on route 44 on Mahatma Gandhi Road on Monday. Police said Bhakti Devi, 60, was taken to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital, where she was pronounced dead. The driver and the conductors of the bus have been arrested. 

 Seven persons were injured after a minibus overturned in Mahestala, on the southern fringes of the city, on Monday. The bus, from Batanagar, was speeding towards Howrah when the driver lost control. The injured were taken to various city hospitals, from where two were released after treatment.

 The 85th birthday of the founder-president of Ananda Marga, Anandamurtiji, was observed at the Tiljala ashram on Monday. 

 A workshop on service tax will be organised by Bharat Chamber of Commerce on May 28. Parthasarathi Shome, advisor to the Union finance minister, is scheduled to inaugurate the workshop.

 Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee released Bappi Lahiri?s album Hand to Hand at Writers? Buildings on Monday. The proceeds from the sale will be donated towards rehabilitation of tsunami survivors.

 Passengers of the Thai Airlines Boeing 747 flight from Bangkok to Munich, which made an emergency landing at Calcutta airport on Sunday, left the city on another flight on Monday. 

